description: From Latin fellifluus, from fel (“gall”) + fluere (“to flow”).

adjectives.description: fellifluous (comparative more fellifluous, superlative most fellifluous)

examples: Truth never reveals itself either to the enthusiast smitten with his own reveries; to the fellifluous fanatic enslaved by his prejudices; to the vain glorious mortal puffed up with his own presumptuous ignorance  […]
